  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAdd type ```byte``` or another solution that allows the creation of a true dynamic size array of type byte.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nCurrently, a fixed-length array is used to generate the ABI for type ```bytes```. In version 0.3.2 the dynamic array was introduced and this is a good opportunity to create a more natural way of creating a dynamic array of type ```byte```.\r\n\r\nCurrent solution that compiles bytes using a fixed-length array:\r\n```vyper\r\n@external\r\ndef onERC721Received(_operator: address, _from: address, _tokenId: uint256, _data: Bytes[4096]) -> bytes4:\r\n    return empty(bytes4)\r\n```\r\n\r\nPossible solution using type ```byte```:\r\n```vyper\r\n@external\r\ndef onERC721Received(_operator: address, _from: address, _tokenId: uint256, _data: DynArray[byte, 1]) -> bytes4:\r\n    return empty(bytes4)\r\n```\r\n\r\nPossible solution using type ```bytes```:\r\n```vyper\r\n@external\r\ndef onERC721Received(_operator: address, _from: address, _tokenId: uint256, _data: bytes) -> bytes4:\r\n    return empty(bytes4)\r\n```\r\n\r\nReference: [byte arrays doc](https://vyper.readthedocs.io/en/stable/types.html#byte-arrays)\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\n## Dependencies\r\n## References\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
